Plug the numbers into the formula for rate of change and simplify.
Rate of change
 = \frac{change in value}{change in time}
 = \frac{15 employees - 12 employees}{2009 - 2008}
 = \frac{15 employees - 12 employees}{1 year}
 = \frac{3 employees}{1 year}
 = 3 employees per year
The rate of change between 2008 and 2009 was 3 employees per year.

